	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64248954"><p>Home sales are the way they are now because holders of 3-4% mortgages aren't willing to take on 7-8% interest rates for slightly better housing.</p><p>In the rental space a major (but not the only) issue is that landlords remember what politicians did to them during COVID lockdowns - they banned evictions, which made paying rent 'optional', with no mechanism to assist apartment complex owners or mom-and-pop landlords. Another issue in the rental space is that apartment complexes are typically highly leveraged, wit<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64248954">

